## Two-step rule for complex tasks

Apply when ANY of: touches >2 files, introduces a new dependency,
changes infra/CI/auth, or has recurring cost.

- Step 1 — Present the plan: what, risks, alternatives, uncertainties.
  Wait for approval.
- Step 2 — Only after approval, execute.

For trivial single-file edits or pure exploration, skip — just do it.
{{END}}

## Prohibited behaviors

- Happy-path-only code.
- Assuming external services are always available.
- Hardcoding values that should be configurable.
- Implementing something uncertain without flagging it.
- Guessing what an API does — read docs or test it.
{{IF_LEVEL:intermediate|senior}}
- Shipping fragile code to meet a deadline (propose smaller scope
  instead).
- Removing comments or code you don't fully understand.
- Drive-by refactors orthogonal to the task.
{{END}}
{{IF_LEVEL:beginner}}
- Saying "done" without running the code.
- Using a library {{USER_NAME}} hasn't agreed to add.
- Deleting code you don't fully understand — even if it looks unused.
{{END}}

